# Graphium

- allow event bus publish like:
    node! {
        # custom event type
        #[publish = EventName]
        async fn get_number() -> u32 {
            7
        }
    }
    or:
    node! {
        # another node! output
        #[publish = EventNodeName]
        async fn get_number() -> u32 {
            7
        }
    }
- allow nodes explicit naming:
    node! {
        #[name = GetNumber]
        async fn get_number() -> u32 {
            7
        }
    }
- allow to unpack references to remove them from ctx after they are read:
    TrainTestSplit(input_features, output_features) -> (&X_train, &X_test, &y_train, &y_test) >>
    Preprocessing(*X_train, *X_test) -> (X_train, X_test)

    Once "Preprocessing" node takes in X_train and X_test consumes them from ctx.
- instead of exposing Graph::export() implement Serialize trait for Graph.
- graphium-core instead of "export" should name feature "dto"
- data buffers analysis
- graphium-ui use wasm to load config at runtime (Docker build compile rust and wasm is provided to rust at runtime)
